23. 
According to ISO 31000: 2009 (International Organization for Standardization), risk 
may be managed or dealt with, as follows: 
 Avoiding the risk by deciding not to start or continue with the activity that 
gives rise to the risk; 
 Accepting or increasing the risk in order to pursue an opportunity; 
 Removing the risk source; 
 Changing the likelihood; 
 Changing the consequences; 
 Sharing the risk with another party or parties (including contracts and risk 
financing);

GUIDANCE NOTE 7 ON THE IMPLEMENTATION OF VARIOUS ASPECTS OF THE FINANCIAL INTELLIGENCE CENTRE ACT, 
2001 (ACT 38 OF 2001) 

